In this article, President Barack Obama issues a proclamation for Mother's Day in 2012. He highlights the importance of mothers in families and communities and honors their sacrifices to ensure their children's success. The article mentions the history of Mother's Day, which was first celebrated in 1913, and the tradition of wearing white carnations to honor mothers. President Obama acknowledges the diverse circumstances in which mothers raise their children and the significant role they play in society. He discusses his efforts to support women's rights and equality, such as the creation of the White House Council on Women and Girls and the signing of the Lilly Ledbetter Fair Pay Act. The article concludes with President Obama urging Americans to show love and gratitude to mothers and to observe Mother's Day with appropriate programs and activities.